Gather information before acting. Rely on `man` and `--help`. Don't truncate or grep the output.
You can run any Python package with `uvx`. E.g: `uvx package-name`. Use the `--help` command to learn more about the package you are using. (e.g: `uvx package-name --help`). You can also use `uvx --with required-package package-name COMMAND` to run the package with additional dependencies.
You can run any npm package with `npx` (e.g: `npx package-name`).
You can run any docker command with `docker` (e.g: `docker run -d -p 8080:8080 image-name`).
Try solving the problems with existing packages to keep things simple.
You can check any website as Markdown with `markitdown` (e.g: `markitdown https://docs.astral.sh/uv/guides/scripts/`). Use that to explore the web and learn more about things you don't know.
If you learn anything useful that you want to remember, ask me to add it to these rules!
